Description: The current explosion of exciting commercial and open-source AI is likely to be followed, within a few years, by creepily superintelligent AI - which top researchers and experts fear could disempower or wipe out humanity. Scientist Max Tegmark describes an optimistic vision for how we can keep AI under control and ensure it's working for us, not the other way around.

Title: The A.I. Dilemma - March 9, 2023
Description: Tristan Harris and Aza Raskin discuss how existing A.I. capabilities already pose catastrophic risks to a functional society, how A.I. companies are caught in a race to deploy as quickly as possible without adequate safety measures, and what it would mean to upgrade our institutions to a post-A.I. world.

Title: Don't Look Up - The Documentary: The Case For AI As An Existential Threat
Description: In the last months, a growing number of AI experts have warned that the current AI Arms Race between OpenAI, Google and some other tech companies, is very dangerous, and might lead to the destruction of the human race. Yet somehow, most people are not aware of this danger.
